{
  "texts": [
    "In the pulsar timing community, it is customary to refer to the dispersion measure with the acronym DM.",
    "Please note that in this paper, DM will exclusively stand for Dark Matter.",
    "This is implemented according to a simple scheme whereby accretion is quenched on the primary SMBH until the binary becomes equal mass.",
    "If/when this occurs, further accretion is equally distributed among the two (now equal mass) binary components.",
    "Most of the signal comes from SMBHBs hosted in massive, lowredshift galaxies (but see Simon 2023), which are relatively gas-poor."
  ]
}